{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χόλ-ος</b>, ὁ, <br /> rarely in physical sense (= later χολή), <b>gall, bile,</b> χόλῳ ἄρα σ᾽ ἔτρεφε μήτηρ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.203. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>gall, bitter anger, wrath,</b> οὐκ Ἀχιλῆϊ χ. φρεσίν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.241; φρενῶν χ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1266 (Lyric poetry); χ. καὶ μῆνις 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.122; χ. λάβε τινά 1.387, etc.; χ. ἔδυ τινά 9.553; χ. δάμασσέ τινα 18.119; χ. ᾕρει τινά 4.23; χ. ἔμπεσε θυμῷ 9.436, etc.; χ. ἔχει θυμόν [prev. work] 675; ὅτε χ. ἵκοι τινά [prev. work] 525; οἰδάνεται κραδίη χόλῳ [prev. work] 646 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χόλον πέσσειν, καταπέσσειν (see entry); σβέσσαι χ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 678; παῦσαι 1.192, etc.; ἐᾶν 9.260; μεθέμεν 1.283; ἐξακέσασθαι 4.36, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.145; ἐκ χόλου μεταστρέψαι ἦτορ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.107 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χόλοιο μεταλήγειν (see. entry); λήγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 221 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χόλου παύθη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 533; ἐκ δὲ χόλω τῶδε λαθοίμεθα 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 23.9; λωφῆσαι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 378; πόσει πάρες χόλον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 1609; opposed to ἐν θυμῷ βάλλεσθαί τινι χόλον 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.50; χ. ἔνθεο θυμῷ 6.326; χ. ἐνέχειν τινί 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.118, 6.119, 8.27; ἔχειν τινί 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1118; ὄρσαι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.23; κινεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 99 (_anapaest meter_); Τυφὼς ἐξαναζέσει χ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 372; χόλου ἄρξασθαι [prev. work] 201 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> <i>subjunctive</i>, a person's <b>rage,</b> χ. Ἥρης, Ἀθηναίης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.119 (see. above), 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.145 (see. above)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: also with <i>genitive</i> <i>object</i>, <b>anger towards</b> or <b>because of</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.335, 15.138 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; or <b>anger for, because of</b> a thing, τίνος χόλον κατ᾽ αὐτῶν ἐγκαλῶν ἐλήλυθα; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 328; ὧν ἔχων χ. [prev. author] “Tr.” 269: also ὄφρα ἑ.. χόλου.. ἀθανάτοις παύσειεν “hymnus ad Cererem” 350, compare 410, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 840. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>bitterness,</b> ἔριδος χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 4.39. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>cause of anger,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 11.381 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus) \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]—In Prose used only by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] and late writers, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Am.” 2. (On the Root, see at {χολή}.) \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9744","accentedUnicode":"χόλος","shortDef":"bitter anger","mediumDef":"bitter anger","stepGloss":"bitter anger","stepTransliteration":"cholos","_step_Type":"word"}]}